-- Mobile security company Lookout raises $150 million
-- 
-- Wed Aug 13, 2014 08:01AM EDT
-- None



Aug 13 (Reuters) - Mobile security company Lookout Inc said it raised $150 million from a group of investors including Morgan Stanley <MS.N> and Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N>.

San Francisco-based Lookout, whose customers include AT&T Inc <T.N> and T-Mobile US Inc <TMUS.N>, said the latest round of financing was led by T.Rowe Price Associates Inc. The company, which plans to extend its platform to large enterprises, was advised by Allen & Co LLC in the funding.